==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solidism
<hw>Sol"id*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>The doctrine that refers all diseases to morbid changes of the
solid parts of the body. It rests on the view that the solids alone are
endowed with vital properties, and can receive the impression of agents
tending to produce disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solidist</ent>⟦br⟧
